OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1780441387
OL,3,CAttorney general 'considering' jail
OL,4,Csentence of Henry Nowak's murderer
OL,6,FDigwa told police that Mr Nowak, who
OL,7,Fhe described as drunk, had racially
OL,8,Fabused him before punching him and
OL,9,Fknocking his turban off.
OL,11,FHe said he had stabbed Mr Nowak to the
OL,12,Fback of his legs in self-defence after
OL,13,FMr Nowak had threatened him and
OL,14,Fgrabbed him by the hair, but said he
OL,15,Fhad not realised at the time he had
OL,16,Fcaused the fatal stab wound to his
OL,17,Fchest.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1780441387
OL,3,CAttorney general 'considering' jail
OL,4,Csentence of Henry Nowak's murderer
OL,6,FBut during the trial, the prosecution
OL,7,Fsaid Digwa had "lied" and deceived
OL,8,Fofficers who attended the scene by
OL,9,Fclaiming that he had not stabbed Mr
OL,10,FNowak despite the student's pleas for
OL,11,Fhelp.
OL,13,FThat led officers to arrest Mr Nowak
OL,14,Fand place him in handcuffs moments
OL,15,Fbefore he collapsed and became
OL,16,Funconscious.
OL,18,FHe died despite their best efforts to
OL,19,Fgive him first aid.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
